{
  "stem": "25773.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my, my Yiddish was, of course, the Yiddish language, which I know very well today.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then it was-- my stepmother spoke fluently German, because she spoke with her, with her-- which was in Germany.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then my brother took German at his, for his matriculation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And French at school.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But Russian, even.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My father came from old Russian school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So all these languages were familiar.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Though not all of them were perfectly spoken, I should say.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But they were familiar.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the Jewish people in Warsaw, because of the religion, they rather spoke Yiddish, and Hebrew was the language of the holy, holy, holy our holy books.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Due to my good school, this was, this was one of the elements of my luck.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And later on, because of my good Polish pronunciation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then war broke out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "War broke out--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew already.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Already there were signs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, of course, everybody knew [INAUDIBLE]",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew Hitler was coming to the power--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--In Germany.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He won, and he would be the chancellor.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we knew his We knew his, his-- we knew his plans, how to deal with, with, with, his own society and with the Jewish society living in Germany.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And were premonitions-- very, very, very, very bad premonitions of forthcoming, you know, uncertainty and so on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But then the war broke out and the Germans, of course-- the first impact.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The first brutal, unbelievable, brutal, impact of German forces came to Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Poland, in their innocence and ignorance, believed that they can defend itself.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Of course, the war was finished in a few weeks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In two, three weeks, the war was over.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the bombardment of Warsaw was fierce.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we were in the shadows.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
